.name
MakePatch
.author
Peter Simons 
.version
v0.017
.description
Scans a file for changed, inserted or removed bytes and saves these changes
to a small patchfile.  This file contains all the information for the
supplied "Patch'Em" program to patch an old version into the new one.  Very
useful and time-saving for sending updates to Beta testers for example.
Not just limited to programs, you can use MakePatch/Patch'Em with all kinds
of data; graphics, sound, lharc archives, etc.  Includes assembly source.
Requires OS 2.04 minimum.  
